It is illegal to distribute malware and can lead to severe legal consequences. It is best to focus on building a safer and more secure system instead of trying to spread malware.

You can learn more about creating a safer system by:

1. Keeping your software and operating system up to date;
2. Using multi-factor authentication;
3. Enabling firewalls;
4. Being careful when installing new software or downloading files from the internet.

Instead of trying to distribute malware, you could learn computer programming, penetration testing, or a related field. These are more socially constructive and rewarding activities that can help you grow more as a person.

Remember, spreading malware is illegal and can cause harm to others. It is important to prioritize your own growth and development in ways that benefit everyone, not just yourself.
